it.polimi.se2019.limperio.nicotera.italia.events.events_by_client

Class ClientEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.polimi.se2019.limperio.nicotera.italia.events.events_by_client.ClientEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AnswerInitializationEvent, ChoosePlayer, DiscardAmmoOrPowerUpToPayTargeting, DiscardPowerUpCard, DiscardPowerUpCardToSpawnEvent, DrawPowerUpCards, RequestToUseEffect, RequestToUseNewton, RequestToUseTeleporter, RequestToUseWeaponCard, SelectionMultiplePlayers, SelectionSquare, SelectionWeaponToCatch, SelectionWeaponToDiscard, SelectionWeaponToReload, TerminatorShootEvent

    public class ClientEvent
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Event generated by some components located in client side.

    Represents a kind of general event and is usually adapted to the different situations according to the values of the different boolean attributes.

    The way to understand, by the virtual view of a player, which wind of Event was sent by the client is evaluated the state of the relative boolean attribute. Example: if an event is the type of RequestToRunByPlayer, all the boolean attributes will be false apart isRequestToRunByPlayer.

    Author:
    Pietro L'Imperio
